ce:section.ce:para:
The pore structure of porous carbon was measured by a surface area and pore size analyzer (ASAP 2460, Micromeritics, American), and the specific surface area was calculated by Brunauer-Emmett-Teller (BET) theory. The total volume (Vt
                        ) was obtained at P/P0
                         = 0.99. The pore size distribution was calculated by the formula of dental functional theory. All samples were degassed at 120 °C for 12 h before analysis.
